transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, yesterday I had, I don't know what I ordered.

Speaker 1: I'm just trying to find out what I ordered and when I'm going to get it.

Speaker 2: Sure, what's your name?

Speaker 1: Roger Parrett, P-A-R-R-E-T-T.

Speaker 2: Your date of birth?

Speaker 1: 6-7-1967.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Okay, you ordered our Viagra, A-G-V, 100 mg. It will be delivered today.

Speaker 2: Oh, will it?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay, now how many is in there?

Speaker 1: You ordered a total of 10 pills.

Speaker 2: 10 pills and that was it because on the thing it said receipt and when I hid it, it had 10 for a certain amount of money and then it had 10 below it on the receipt that said 70 some dollars for 10. What was that?

Speaker 1: For 10 pills, you paid a total of $63.95.

Speaker 2: That was the one I was looking at. $63. Now is that every month?

Speaker 1: Your prescription is for every month, yes.

Speaker 2: So, let's see. Okay, it will work out fine.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay, they'll be delivered today?

Speaker 1: Yeah, they'll be delivered today.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 1: You're welcome. Have a good day, Roger.

Speaker 2: You too. Bye.

Speaker 1: Thank you. Bye-bye.
